1. Virtual function: A normal virtual function provides basic implementation and can be overriden. It has choice for overriding    the function.Not mandatorily required to override the function.
Ex:
class Animal
{
public:
    virtual void sound()
    {
        cout << "Animal sound";
    }
};



2. Pure vitual function:Doesnt provide any basic implementation and mandatorily has to be overriden (forces derived classes to override) making the class abstract class.
 Ex:
 class Animal
{
public:
    virtual void sound() = 0;  ->Animal is an abstract class.
};                                      


